Comment
As provided, the input file is setup to calculate scattering by two 
particles (spheroids) at a wavelength of 0.2 * Pi micrometer. The T 
matrices of the particles are read from the files FileTmatPart = 
'../TMATFILES/TProlA4B2.dat' and FileTmatPart = 
'../TMATFILES/TProlA4B2.dat', i.e., the particles are identical. 
The maximum expansion and azimuthal orders of the particles are 
NrankPart = 10 and MrankPart = 4, while the relative refractive index
with respect to the ambient medium is 1.5. The positions of the 
particles with respect to the coordinate system of the cluster are 
given by xPart = yPart = zPart = 0.0 and xPart = 0.0, yPart = zPart 
= 0.565685424 micrometer. The Euler angles are alphaPart = betaPart 
= gammaPart = 0° and alphaPart = betaPart = 45°, gammaPart = 0°. 
Convergence is achieved for Nrank = 21 and Mrank = 19.









